      <h3 id="scroll-link-2"><%=image_tag('kitty.jpg', alt: "Home", width:25) %> Creating a Project</h3>
      <h2>What kind of project can I create?</h2>
      <p>Projects on CrowdKitty must be designed with a clear and deliverable end goal that will specifically benefit your local community in some way. Things like building a playground, helping out a local charity, or putting on a community event are just the ticket for our jolly little site. However, there are a few strings for obvious reasons. For example, we only accept projects based in the UK. Please see 'Terms and Conditions' page for full details.</p>
      <br>
      <h2>How do I create a project?</h2>
      <p>Anyone that meets our Guidelines is eligible to create a project on CrowdKitty. Just click the 'Create Project' link in the menu bar above to begin your project. Just fill out the form that pops up on that page with all the relevant details. If you want to add rewards, you can do that after you've created your project.</p>
      <br>
      <h2>Can projects raise more than their target?</h2>
      <p>Of course! As soon as you reach your fundraising target your campaign will be decelared successful but we won't stop further pledges. You can raise as much money as possible in the alloted time that you have set for the project. However, you have to satisfy both the backers and CrowdKitty that this extra money is being used in a worthy manner. It must be spent towards the cause it was intended. For further information on this or for some general advice you can contact CrowdKitty and speak to one of our lovely advisors.</p>
    </section>
